<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FF4F6AF0FF4B9AAB1DB8B6B8" pageId="180" pageNumber="942" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFF4F6AF0FF4B9AAB1DB8B6B8" blockId="180.[181,1391,3196,3476]" pageId="180" pageNumber="942">
Subgenus Pizonyx; 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF4F6AF0FE479AAB1C2AB621" authorityName="E. Geoffroy Saint-Hilaire" authorityYear="1806" box="[443,554,3314,3347]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Vespertilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="180" pageNumber="942" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="albescens">albescens</taxonomicName>
species group. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF4F6AF0FCFE9AAB1DBAB621" baseAuthorityName="Peters" baseAuthorityYear="1867" box="[770,954,3314,3347]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="180" pageNumber="942" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="oxyotus">Myotis oxyotus</taxonomicName>
was considered a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF4F6AF0FF4B9B431F5EB609" authorityName="Waterhouse" authorityYear="1838" box="[183,350,3354,3387]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Vespertilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="180" pageNumber="942" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="chiloensis">M. chiloensis</taxonomicName>
, but studies based on morphology and molecular data indicate clear distinction between the two. Studies of molecular data indicated that subspecies gardneri might be a distinct species. Two subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
